        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 8 at 10:30AM CDT by NWS San Angelo TX</headline>
        <description>At 1030 AM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Menard, moving east at 35 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Menard, Calf Creek, Us-83 Near The Menard-Concho County Line, Us-
190 Near The Menard-Mcculloch County Line, The Intersection Of Us-
190 And Ranch Road 1311, and The Intersection Of Us-
83 And Highway 29.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
